s, on behalf of the organiser and client.</li>\n\t\t<li>The Apps and their services are provided free of charge to delegates.</li>\n\t\t<li>In order to benefit from all service features of the app it is recommended for Congress members and delegates who attend any Conference or Meeting or meeting to register via entering their access code or badge number. This can be done via a scan of their badge barcode with the scanner feature in the app or through manual entry.</li>\n\t\t<li>A valid access and badge code is required to log into for the App for any particular congress, event or meeting. If you register you will be asked to review and update your personal information that has been saved on the registration database for this event. If you register upon arrival at any Meeting or Event, a time lag may occur until your personal details are available in the app from the registration database.</li>\n\t\t<li>When you register for the App your personal data is saved and stored by Navus on a secure server in Switzerland. Navus will process your data in accordance with applicable laws, including but not limited to, data privacy laws. Your updated personal data and other records may be used to update the THE ORGANISER / CLIENT delegate registration database. THE ORGANISER / CLIENT may use your data to inform you of its activities, including, but not limited to, informing you about future THE ORGANISER / CLIENT Meetings</li>\n\t\t<li>Some of your App usage, including but not limited to the use of modules and page views, downloads, duration of sessions and searches will be captured and stored by Navus. The captured data will used to\n\t\t<ol>\n\t\t\t<li>produce consolidated statistics and reports to improve App services and other services for future events.</li>\n\t\t\t<li>report consolidated statistics of sponsor banner impressions and click rates to sponsors</li>\n\t\t\t<li>enhance your user experience by developing a user profile to personalize content recommendations that can be accessed via the THE ORGANISER / CLIENT digital services.</li>\n\t\t</ol>\n\t\t</li>\n\t\t<li>If you don&rsquo;t want that your data is used as in section 1.7 don&rsquo;t register and don&rsquo;t log into the app.</li>\n\t\t<li>You are able to use the app without logging in, however certain features are not available without being logged in.</li>\n\t\t<li>Navus will not make individual user details or personal information available to any third parties.</li>\n\t\t<li>For questions and user support please visit the help desk during a meeting. The service capability of the help desk is limited and may not include technical support that is specific to your mobile device.</li>\n\t\t<li>Navus is acting as a third party supplier and is not liable for any issues that occur as a result of delegates using the App and its provided services, including but not limited to: inaccurate program or congress data, map errors, connection issues, synchronization issues, bugs, data errors, loading time, registration errors, inaccurate E-materials service data, distorted displays etc.</li>\n\t\t<li>Navus and THE ORGANISER / CLIENT reserve the right to discontinue the App and related services at any time and without prior notification.</li>\n\t\t<li>You agree with the terms regarding the processing of your personal data by Navus Consulting GmbH and THE ORGANISER / CLIENT. You have the right to view your data, request changes to your data, and request the deletion of your data saved in the database at any time by contacting Navus at the following e-mail address:&nbsp;<a href=\"mailto:support@e-materials.com\">support@e-materials.com</a></li>\n\t</ol>\n\t</li>\n\t<li><strong>Meeting and Event Portals</strong>\n\t<ol>\n\t\t<li>Portal accessible via e-materials.com or navus.ch are intended to allow registered users to easily access educational content from THE ORGANISER / CLIENT activities and to engage in online dialogues.</li>\n\t\t<li>The portals have been developed by Navus Consulting GmbH, Klingentalstrasse 47, CH-4057 Basel, Switzerland (&ldquo;Navus&rdquo;), and are licensed to the The Organiser / Client.</li>\n\t\t<li>By registering with any portal the user confirms that all data provided are truthful and correct and if he/she is a delegate of a conference, meeting or event and that the access code and badge is valid for the day on which he/she registered (&quot;Delegate&quot;).</li>\n\t\t<li>By registering on a portal, the user confirms that he/she consents to provide the requested personal information.</li>\n\t\t<li>The user&rsquo;s personal data after entering a badge may pre-fill a registration form. The date appear as stored in the THE ORGANISER / CLIENT registration database. Delegate has previously agreed within the registration for the THE ORGANISER / CLIENT congress or meeting that their data will be stored.</li>\n\t\t<li>The User needs to accept these Terms &amp; Conditions to complete the registration on a Portal expressly; with the acceptation of the terms and conditions by THE ORGANISER / CLIENT the Delegate and User confirms knowledge of the Terms &amp; Conditions by Navus expressly and unambiguously.</li>\n\t\t<li>Data will be stored on dedicated and secure Navus servers in Switzerland. Navus stores the data for reference and does not disclose the data to any other third party.</li>\n\t\t<li>By registering with a Portal the user agrees that his/her personal data and specifically his/her e-mail address are handed over to THE ORGANISER / CLIENT. THE ORGANISER / CLIENT and Navus collect and process user&rsquo;s data in accordance with the applicable laws, including but not limited to, data privacy laws.</li>\n\t\t<li>User hereby expressly and unambiguously agrees that User&#39;s personal data may be collected and processed and will be solely stored by Navus. Navus will collect and process User&rsquo;s data in accordance with the applicable laws, including but not limited to, data privacy laws. User agrees expressly and unambiguously that Navus and THE ORGANISER / CLIENT may use his/her data for\n\t\t<ol>\n\t\t\t<li>Updating the THE ORGANISER / CLIENT database</li>\n\t\t\t<li>Marketing and Sales activities including, but not limited to, following up with Users about User&#39;s stated and deducted areas of interest and requests, sending sponsor messages, promoting educational activities, informing about Navus services related to meetings and events.</li>\n\t\t\t<li>Creating user profiles to develop and share personalised content and event recommendations</li>\n\t\t</ol>\n\t\t</li>\n\t\t<li>Navus and THE ORGANISER / CLIENT will not communicate User&#39;s personal data or User&rsquo;s profile or User&rsquo;s personal recommendations to any other third parties or make them perceptible or make them available directly or through any kind of medium.</li>\n\t\t<li>If User does not wish to have his/her updated personal data entered into the database of the assigned industry exhibitor, or to receive any further information from the assigned industry exhibitor or to receive personal content recommendations User must refrain from registration with our websites and portals.</li>\n\t\t<li>At the annual THE ORGANISER / CLIENT congress and at some other smaller THE ORGANISER / CLIENT meetings a help desk is available for general questions about the Portal.</li>\n\t\t<li>Navus is acting as a third party supplier and is not liable for any issues that occur as a result of Users using a portal and its services, including but not limited to a slow internet connection, no internet connection, frequent cut outs, limited page loads, data transaction errors, distorted displays, etc. Navus and THE ORGANISER / CLIENT may not be held liable in case of force majeure, nor should they be held liable for any data loss, e-mail issues, technical issues, or issues with data synchronisations over the internet.</li>\n\t\t<li>User explicitly agrees with the present Terms &amp; Conditions by THE ORGANISER / CLIENT regarding the processing of User&rsquo;s personal data by Navus Consulting GmbH, THE ORGANISER / CLIENT and any affiliates. User has the right to consult his/her data in an intelligible form or to request changes to his/her personal details contained in the database at any time, by contacting Navus at the following e-mail address&nbsp;<a href=\"mailto:support@e-materials.com\">support@e-materials.com</a></li>\n\t</ol>\n\t</li>\n\t<li><strong>E-materials Services</strong>\n\t<ol>\n\t\t<li>The E-material service is accessible via THE ORGANISER / CLIENT&rsquo;s digital services on apps and websites. The E-material service allows a) registered THE ORGANISER / CLIENT Congress members and Delegates attending an THE ORGANISER / CLIENT Congress or THE ORGANISER / CLIENT meeting, b) THE ORGANISER / CLIENT full members and c) invited or paying guests to access available speaker slides and webcasts, posters, abstracts and articles of the THE ORGANISER / CLIENT scientific and educational program and other THE ORGANISER / CLIENT materials from other content sources that were made available by THE ORGANISER / CLIENT for this service.</li>\n\t\t<li>Users need an account to use the E-materials service and provide a valid badge or access code.</li>\n\t\t<li>The E-materials service is free of charge for users with a valid badge or valid access credentials. THE ORGANISER / CLIENT may charge a fee to other users to access all or parts of the available E-materials.</li>\n\t\t<li>By registering for this service you confirm that you are a registered THE ORGANISER / CLIENT Congress members or an THE ORGANISER / CLIENT member, an invited guests or a user who paid for the service. Guests can be invited by THE ORGANISER / CLIENT, the sponsor of the services and (if activated) via the &lsquo;Invite my peers&rsquo; feature on the website.</li>\n\t\t<li>Materials that are available to access are supplied only for scientific and educational purposes. You can access them only for your personal use for non-commercial purposes. No modification or further reproduction of the content is permitted without the prior written permission of THE ORGANISER / CLIENT and the author.</li>\n\t\t<li>Reusing any material or parts of the material requires the proper citation of all original authors. The content may otherwise not be copied or used in any way.</li>\n\t\t<li>All materials are subject to copyright. THE ORGANISER / CLIENT and the author(s) will use reasonable efforts to include up-to-date and accurate information in the materials, but THE ORGANISER / CLIENT and Navus make no representations, warranties, or assurances as to the accuracy, currency, or completeness of the information provided. Furthermore, materials may represent a summary of independent evaluations and opinions of the authors and contributors, including, where applicable, material relating to clinical cases, which reflect the clinical judgment and opinions of the physician(s) in selecting specific products for these cases.</li>\n\t\t<li>THE ORGANISER / CLIENT and Navus shall not be liable for any damages or injury resulting from your access to, or inability to access, the materials, from your reliance on any information provided through the materials or for any possible inaccurate or misleading data or statements. Neither does THE ORGANISER / CLIENT and Navus endorse the content or the use of any product in any way.</li>\n\t\t<li>A scientific session may contain more than one presentation. Not all presentations nor all slides that a speaker presented may be available. THE ORGANISER / CLIENT and Navus will only provide materials that are available for the E-material services. Materials are considered available if the speaker provided his/her consent captured in the speaker office, submitted online or via printed consent forms that his/her slides, articles, posters and publications can be used for publication via the E-material services.</li>\n\t\t<li>THE ORGANISER / CLIENT can change the availability of any material at any time without prior notice.</li>\n\t\t<li>Navus and THE ORGANISER / CLIENT reserve the right to discontinue the services for all or individual users at any time and without prior notice.</li>\n\t\t<li>If a user logs on to his/her account and accesses materials all online activities will be stored in dedicated databases.</li>\n\t\t<li>The creation of an account is required to access any materials. If you don&rsquo;t visit a portal and don&rsquo;t create an account you will not be able to access E-materials. You agree that THE ORGANISER / CLIENT or Navus may contact you via email and send you reminders about your account status.</li>\n\t\t<li>Your personal data is collected and will be stored by Navus and THE ORGANISER / CLIENT in a central database. THE ORGANISER / CLIENT and Navus will process your data in accordance with the applicable laws, including but not limited to, data privacy laws. THE ORGANISER / CLIENT may use your data to inform you of its activities, including, but not limited to, informing you about future THE ORGANISER / CLIENT meetings.</li>\n\t\t<li>Your E-materials services usage including account log in, access, material views, ratings and other activities will be captured by Navus and THE ORGANISER of the event that you are attending. Navus will not make any personal and individual details about the usage of the E-material available to any third party.</li>\n\t\t<li>For questions and user support a help desk maybe available on site during an THE ORGANISER / CLIENT congress or a meeting. The service capability of the help desk is limited and may not cover all specific questions you may have about sessions and their content.</li>\n\t\t<li>It is allowed for logged in Users to ask questions and send messages to Speakers of a session via the Messaging module of the E-materials portal and the related app feature. All questions and replies are published and visible for all logged in users. You agree, through your use of this service, that you will not use this Question and Messaging tool to submit any question to the speaker, which is knowingly defamatory, threatening, abusive, inaccurate, hateful, profane, obscene, vulgar or sexually oriented. Do not submit any question or message with content that you do not have the right to submit under any law. You remain solely responsible for the content of your questions and messages, and you agree to indemnify and hold Navus and their agents with respect to any claim based upon transmission of your questions. Navus and THE ORGANISER / CLIENT accept no responsibility or liability for the content that is submitted on this question tool or the replies that are provided by the speaker. Navus will only use the content that created by the Q&amp;A module to produce consolidated statistics for THE ORGANISER / CLIENT and to enhance personalised content recommendations to users.</li>\n\t\t<li>Materials made available by speakers may be published, depending on the availability of the electronic file up to a few days after the presentation.</li>\n\t\t<li>You explicitly agree with the present terms regarding the processing of your personal data by Navus Consulting GmbH and THE ORGANISER / CLIENT. You have the right to consult your data or to request changes to, or request the deletion of, your personal details contained in the database at any time, by contacting Navus at the following e-mail address&nbsp;<a href=\"mailto:support@e-materials.com\">support@e-materials.com</a></li>\n\t</ol>\n\t</li>\n\t<li><strong>Delegate Lead Apps</strong>\n\t<ol>\n\t\t<li>The delegate lead applications are licensed to exhibitors of THE ORGANISER / CLIENT congresses and meetings for the duration of each meeting.</li>\n\t\t<li>A lead application is intended to allow health care professionals to easily provide information, share areas of interest and request follow ups with industry exhibitors during THE ORGANISER / CLIENT congresses and meetings and for industry exhibitors to easily gather, store and process that delegate information (&quot;the Delegate Lead App&quot;).</li>\n\t\t<li>By registering with the THE ORGANISER / CLIENT App Delegate confirms that he/she is a delegate with a badge that is valid for the day on which he/she registered (&quot;Delegate&quot;).</li>\n\t\t<li>By registering on the licensed Delegate Lead App, the Delegate confirms that he consents to provide the requested information to the assigned industry exhibitor.</li>\n\t\t<li>The assigned industry exhibitor may scan Delegate information via the iPad Delegate Lead App. The Delegate&#39;s personal data, as stored in the THE ORGANISER / CLIENT registration database, appears on screen (Delegate has previously agreed within registration for the congress at THE ORGANISER / CLIENT for their data to be captured by assigned industry exhibitors with a scan). The assigned industry exhibitor asks Delegate if personal data is correct, edits his/her wrong data, enters missing data directly on the interface. The assigned industry exhibitor captures other data (survey, interest areas, request to receive info materials, local follow up requests etc.).</li>\n\t\t<li>The Delegate needs to accept these Terms &amp; Conditions to complete the transaction expressly; with the acceptation of the terms and conditions by Navus the Delegate confirms knowledge of the Terms &amp; Conditions by Navus expressly and unambiguously.</li>\n\t\t<li>Data will be stored on the iPad Delegate Lead App (the device shall be provided by assigned industry exhibitor) within the Navus Delegate Lead App and is transferred to dedicated and secure Navus servers in Switzerland. After the congress Navus sends all captured data via an Excel template to one contact person of the assigned industry exhibitor. Navus stores the data for reference and does not disclose the data to any other third party. The assigned industry exhibitor stores the data and may share it with affiliates and country organisations.</li>\n\t\t<li>By registering with the Delegate Lead App Delegate agree that his/her personal data and specifically his/her e-mail address are handed over to the assigned industry exhibitor. The assigned industry exhibitor will collect and process Delegate&#39;s data in accordance with the applicable laws, including but not limited to, data privacy laws.</li>\n\t\t<li>Delegate hereby expressly and unambiguously agrees that Delegate&#39;s personal data may be collected and processed and will be solely stored by Navus. Navus will collect and process Delegate&#39;s data in accordance with the applicable laws, including but not limited to, data privacy laws. Delegate&#39;s updated personal data and information provided may be used to update the assigned industry exhibitor&rsquo;s database. Delegate agrees expressly and unambiguously that the assigned industry exhibitor may use his/her data for Marketing and Sales activities including, but not limited to, following up with Delegate about Delegate&#39;s stated areas of interest and requests.</li>\n\t\t<li>Navus and THE ORGANISER / CLIENT will not communicate Delegate&#39;s personal data to any other third parties or make them perceptible or make them available directly or through any kind of medium.</li>\n\t\t<li>If Delegate does not wish to have his/her updated personal data entered into the database of the assigned industry exhibitor, or to receive any further information from the assigned industry exhibitor Delegate must refrain from registration with the Delegate Lead App.</li>\n\t\t<li>At larger meeting a help desk is usually available for general questions.</li>\n\t\t<li>Navus and THE ORGANISER / CLIENT each or together reserve the right to discontinue the Delegate Lead App service for all or individual Delegates and assigned industry exhibitors for any reason at any time and without prior notice</li>\n\t\t<li>Navus is acting as a third party supplier and is not liable for any issues that occur as a result of Delegates using the Delegate Lead